<TITLE> Cabinet approves new border guards law </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 1 (bdnews24.com)  The cabinet on Monday approved in principle the draft Border Guards Bangladesh Act 2010, that sets death as the maximum penalty for mutiny. It also formed a six-member committee for further scrutiny of the proposed law, with the prime minister's two advisers HT Imam and Mashiur Rahman. Other members of the committee are the prime minister's principal secretary, cabinet secretary, law and home secretaries. The committee has been asked to submit its report at the next cabinet meeting, the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told a press briefing after the weekly cabinet meeting. The government moved to formulate the new act after the bloody BDR mutiny last February in which over 70 people were killed, including 57 army officers deputed to the border force. The cabinet meeting also approved Bangladesh Child Labour Prevention Policy 2010. bdne
